description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is eligible for a £3000 new hire bonus. An initial payment of £1000 will be paid in the first 6 months and a final payment of £2000 will be paid 1 year after your start date. New hires to part-time roles will receive a pro-rata bonus.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Located in the vibrant Cathedral City of Peterborough, Maple ward is an assessment and treatment ward for older adults who have acute mental health needs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Registered Mental Health Nurses, but you can be a Registered General Nurse(RGN) who has knowledge and experience in mental health. We would be keen to hear from applicants who share our vision of continually enhancing the patient experience of older adults. We welcome newly qualified staff; who will be supported by preceptorship program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cavell Centre is a state of the art unit which will offer patients purpose built accommodation with single en-suite bedrooms. It includes adult acute psychiatric wards, a psychiatric intensive care unit, older people’s mental health unit and a specialist service for people with learning disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Part-time post, salary will be pro-rata.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sidi Akpoyibo, Ward manager &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sidi.akpoyibo@cpft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
